The paper discusses the spread of influence in complex networks, specifically in online social networks, which falls under the category of social networks and information diffusion. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a modified algorithm for influence maximization, which involves data structures and algorithms, falling under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of the model for identifying influential content creators, which involves artificial intelligence and machine learning, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of the model for real-world social media datasets, which involves cybersecurity, falling under cs.CYBER (Cryptology and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the submodularity of the influence function, which falls under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
